# Repo structure, route features, and exports

Canonical write-up: **`docs/coding-guidebook.md`**. Layer boundaries: **`ui-layer-boundaries.mdc`**. i11n: **`i11n-colocation.mdc`**.

Treat **`src/app/(task)/`** as the **reference template** for other product areas under `src/app/(…)/**`: group by route segment, colocate UI, context, and helpers the same way.

## Reference tree: `src/app/(task)/` (current)

| Path | Role |
|---|---|
| **`page.tsx`** | Route entry: providers, breakpoint/intent split, composes layouts; mount **long-lived** clients here when switching child layouts must not remount them (e.g. map). |
| **`context/`** | Segment-scoped providers and hooks (e.g. `TaskBrowseProvider.tsx`); optional `index.ts` for re-exports. |
| **`helpers/`** | Pure helpers and segment-local types (e.g. `taskBrowseHelpers.ts`, `taskBrowseFilters.types.ts`) consumed by `components/` or `context/`. |
| **`components/`** | Feature UI; **`components/index.ts`** is **auto-generated** (see exports below). |
| **`components/(web)/`** | Desktop / split-view-only UI (e.g. `WebLayout`, `TaskList`, web-only filter panels). |
| **`components/(mobile)/`** | Small-viewport-only UI (e.g. `MobileLayout`, bottom sheets, carousels). |
| **`components/`** (files next to `(web)` / `(mobile)`) | **Cross-breakpoint** pieces: context-wired wrappers, primitives reused by both layouts, map shell (`TaskMap` / `TaskBrowseMapLayer`), shared filter summaries (`TaskTag.tsx`), etc. |
| **`tasks/create/`** | Nested route: `page.tsx`, schema, and **`tasks/create/components/`** for create-flow sections (colocate with that route). |
| **`graphql/`** (beside `page.tsx`) | Route-owned GraphQL operations — see **`graphql-route-colocation.mdc`**. |
| **`task/[slug]/`** | Dynamic route with its own `page.tsx` and colocated `components/` as needed. |

New domains should mirror this: **`(web)`** / **`(mobile)`** when UI forks by viewport; **`helpers/`** and **`context/`** at the segment when logic or types are shared across pages in that folder.

## `page.tsx` (any `src/app/**/page.tsx`)

- **`page.tsx` is the screen.** Metadata (via colocated `layout.tsx` when the page is a client component), data loading, route orchestration, and page composition live here — not in a sibling `PageContent.tsx` / `*Page.tsx` that `page.tsx` only re-exports.
- **Never** create `PageContent.tsx` (or `BillingPage.tsx`, `FooPageLayout.tsx`, etc.) whose sole job is holding the route body so `page.tsx` can `return <PageContent />`. Merge that body into `page.tsx`.
- When the route needs hooks / Apollo / browser APIs, mark **`page.tsx` with `'use client'`**. Put `generateMetadata` in a thin colocated **`layout.tsx`** (server) that returns `children` — Next.js cannot put `generateMetadata` and `'use client'` in the same file.
- Extract **colocated `components/`** for **sections and widgets** (cards, forms, sidebars, maps) — reuse, `(web)` / `(mobile)` forks, or real decomposition. Naming alone is not a reason to split the whole screen out of `page.tsx`.

### Bad

```tsx
// page.tsx — do not do this
export default function Page() {
  return <PageContent />
}
```

### Good

```tsx
// page.tsx — route body + logic live here ('use client' when needed)
export default function Page() {
  const data = useMyQuery()
  return (
    <>
      <SectionA ... />
      <SectionB ... />
    </>
  )
}

// layout.tsx — optional; only for generateMetadata when page.tsx is a client component
export async function generateMetadata() { ... }
export default function Layout({ children }) { return children }
```


## `components/` under a route segment

- **`(web)/`** — Layouts and panels only used in the desktop / split experience.
- **`(mobile)/`** — Layouts and controls only used on small screens.
- **Root of `components/`** — Public entry / screen orchestrator (e.g. `ProfileHub.tsx`, `SearchScreen.tsx`) + colocated `*.stories.tsx` for that entry; optional `index.ts` barrel.
- **Concern subfolders** (same idea as `src/ui/Header/`): group related pieces — e.g. `hero/`, `cards/`, `edit/`, `layout/`, `widgets/`, `sections/`, `shared/`, `inputs/`, `steps/`. Keep stories next to the component they cover; do **not** story internal sub-pieces when the parent entry story already exercises them.
- Do **not** leave a flat dump of many unrelated `.tsx` files at the components root when they cluster by concern.
- Do **not** duplicate the same markup under `(web)` and `(mobile)` unless it truly diverges; lift shared UI to the **components root** or a shared subfolder.

## UI atom/reuse architecture

Three conceptual layers (all shared UI lives under **`src/ui`**):

| Layer | Path | Examples |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Primitives | `src/ui/<Name>/` → `@ui` | Button, Card, Avatar, Drawer, FormField, LanguageSwitcher (presentational) |
| Shell chrome | `src/ui/Header`, `src/ui/Dock` | Header, Dock, AccountMenu, NotificationsDrawer |
| Feature | `src/app/**/components` | TaskCard, MeAvatar, TaskStatusPill |

- Route/feature code should **compose from `@ui` first**.
- Exception: plain **`Text`** can be used directly from Chakra when a dedicated UI wrapper is unnecessary.

### Reuse-first workflow (required)

1. **Search for existing UI first** (`src/ui`) before creating new scoped markup/components.
2. If a similar UI component exists, **reuse it**.
3. If similar but not enough, **extend the existing `src/ui` component** with reusable props (prefer optional props over one-off forks).
4. Only create a new `src/ui` component when no suitable atom/reusable element exists.
5. App-aware chrome → `src/ui/Header` / `src/ui/Dock` (same folder shape as primitives + colocated `i11n.json`).

### Rules for new UI components

- New `src/ui` folders follow **`ui-layer-boundaries.mdc`** (`<Name>.tsx`, optional `i11n.json`, `ui/<Name>` story).
- Use generic naming and prop APIs for primitives (avoid task/domain-specific prop names unless truly global).
- Keep variants configurable through props/tokens instead of duplicating components.
- Primitives: no Apollo / Me store / pathname chrome. Shell chrome folders may.
- Connected adapters for primitives (cookie, Apollo) live outside `src/ui` when needed (e.g. `src/i18n/LanguageSwitcher.tsx`).

### Extract universal primitives; keep route adapters thin

- If a route-scoped component is really a **generic widget** (progress bar, stepper, dropdown/popover, etc.), **extract the universal piece to `src/ui`** with a data-agnostic prop API.
- The route keeps a **thin adapter** that reads its context/data and renders the `src/ui` primitive (e.g. `WorkerSetupStepper` → `<Stepper>`; `MeAvatar` → `<Avatar srcCandidates={…} />`). Adapters need no story.
- **Feature menus compose layout primitives.** `AccountMenu` (under `src/ui/Header`) builds on `Dropdown` / `Drawer`.

### Storybook grouping (see `storybook-story-conventions` skill)

Stories are titled **by source ownership**:

| Source | Title | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| `src/ui` | `ui/*` | `ui/Input`, `ui/Header`, `ui/Dock`, `ui/LanguageSwitcher` |
| `src/app/(…)` | folder path (strip groups + `components/`) | `marketing/Header`, `task/TaskCard`, `worker/setup/WorkerSetupBioComposer` |

Rules:

- **No `form/*` / `Components/*` / `Patterns/*` / `layout/*` / `shell/*` titles.** Everything under `src/ui` is `ui/*`.
- **No duplicate primitive stories.** One story file per universal primitive.
- **Universal-first.** Generic widgets live in `src/ui` with `ui/*` stories; route adapters get **no story**.
- **One story per non-universal feature component.** Do **not** story internal sub-components — exercise them through the parent.

### Context colocation (any route provider)

- **`WebLayout` / `MobileLayout`-style shells** should mostly **compose** structure (position, z-index, flex) and mount children.
- **Leaf or focused components** should call **`useYourData()` / `useYourLayout()`** (or your segment’s hooks) where they render—not only in the parent to forward props.
- Prefer **small wrappers** next to the control (e.g. a button component that reads layout UI from context) over drilling from the shell.
- **Avoid:** shell calls context solely to pass the same props into a child that could call the hook itself.

## Barrel exports (`bun run exports-gen`)

- Feature code stays grouped **by route/domain** (e.g. `src/app/(task)`).
- Folders with an auto-generated **`index.ts`** must be listed in **`EXPORT_CONFIGS`** in **`scripts/generate-exports.ts`** (currently: **`src/ui`**, **`src/app/(task)/components`**).
- After **adding** a registered folder or **moving** modules between registered folders, run **`bun run exports-gen`**.
- Do **not** manually maintain generated barrel files where the header marks them auto-generated.
- Nested folders (e.g. `tasks/create/components/`) are **not** in `EXPORT_CONFIGS` unless you add them; use local imports or add a config entry if a barrel is required.

## Checklist

- [ ] New exportable folder added to **`EXPORT_CONFIGS`** when it needs a root barrel.
- [ ] **`bun run exports-gen`** run after moves/adds under registered folders.
- [ ] Affected imports updated to barrel paths where the codebase uses `@/` / package barrels for that folder.
- [ ] No **`PageContent` / pass-through page module** — route body lives in `page.tsx`.
- [ ] No **view-only** split: extra component files under the route justify reuse, layout fork, or real decomposition—not only moving one screen out of `page.tsx`.
- [ ] Client `page.tsx` + metadata → colocated `layout.tsx` with `generateMetadata`.
